ogy provide a stark backdrop to creative output. A further innovation is the inclusion of essays on public art, natural heritage interpretation and the visualisation and aesthetic impact of wind farms. The book will be of interest to writers, artists, students and researchers in the environmental humanities and those with a general interest in the cultural response to the environment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEcocriticism. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aclimate patterns.  acreative partnership.  aday-to-day environments.  adeath.  aecocriticism.  aecomusicology.  aenvironmentalism.  ahigh theory.  ahuman denial.  amundane experience.  anatural heritage interpretation.  aphotomontage.  aradical landscape poems.  awindfarm.1 aAllen, Aaron S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarry, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarry, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCazeaux, Clive, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDarwell, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGross, Philip, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLean, Patti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPearson, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRopek, Eve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSquire, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTarlo, Harriet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTucker, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWelstead, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4